COVID-19 cases have plateaued in Ohio over the past few weeks but not declined, and the state has more than 8,000 cases.
Maine and much of the country have had difficulties increasing testing, but testing volume has improved compared to March.
In addition to increased testing, states need to have the capacity to trace all or most contacts, experts say.